theorem Topology.closure_union_closure_compl_eq_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    closure A ∪ closure (Aᶜ) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  -- `interior A` is contained in `closure A`.
  have h_int_subset : interior A ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
  -- We already know `interior A ∪ closure (Aᶜ) = univ`.
  have h_union :=
    Topology.interior_union_closure_compl_eq_univ (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Prove the desired equality by showing mutual inclusion.
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro _; simp
  · intro _
    -- Place `x` in `interior A ∪ closure (Aᶜ)` via `h_union`.
    have hx_union : x ∈ interior A ∪ closure (Aᶜ) := by
      have : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by simp
      simpa [h_union] using this
    -- Transfer membership to the required union.
    cases hx_union with
    | inl hxInt =>
        exact Or.inl (h_int_subset hxInt)
    | inr hxClCompl =>
        exact Or.inr hxClCompl

theorem Topology.interior_subset_of_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hAB : A ⊆ closure B) :
    interior A ⊆ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  exact hAB (interior_subset hx)
